name: Steel Fixing Checklist
Structural Element
Anti-burst tied to top steel reinforcement, with enough cover for concrete
Quality Check - As per structural engineering plans Reinforcement size correct, spacing does not exceed maximum allowed, position within tolerance - As per structural engineering plans
Starter bars correctly set out and adequately secured
Lap length and location acceptable - As per structural engineering plans
Concrete cover within tolerance - As per structural engineering plans
Reo not cut or bent for ease of installation
All openings sufficiently trimmed, re-entry bars installed (to avoid cracking) - As per structural engineering plans
Reo bars sufficiently tied and supported (minimal deflection / does not come apart when stood on)
Reo bars clean, free from rust and salt etc.
Reinforcement tied as per structural engineer drawings
Visual inspection by TSG employee completed
Engineer Inspection – all rectifications made as per engineer mark-up prior concrete pour
Loose tie wire and trimmings have been removed from formwork deck prior to pour.
All production tags have been fully removed prior to pour.
All bar caps installed where required.
Starter bars, Ripboxes, Couplers and the like correctly set out and adequately secured
Comments (Re Engineer Inspection Report)
Photo of engineer report
